New Features and Important Changes, r2.2 vs r2.1

Author(s) :  Alexey PETROV

2010-04-04

* Adjusting to the "common configuration system" (confFoam package)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
"confFoam" is a "common configuration package" for the realted OpenFOAM (Open
Source CFD Toolbox, see http://sourceforge.net/projects/foam/ ) developement. 
The neccessity for defintion of such kind of functionality appears from the
issue that OpenFOAM referece build system does not provide corresponding
capabilities. As result of lack of the configuration capabilties OpenFOAM
users/developers strugle with compilation procidure trying to discover reasons
for this or that failure.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------

New Features and Important Changes, v2.0

Author(s) :  Alexey PETROV

2009-04-15

1. Introduction
---------------
This document briefly explains some of the most important changes made
since the release of foam2med-r1.2. The goal is to provide information for
people who want to upgrade an older foam2med interface to the new version.

2. Post-processing capabilities
-------------------------------
The foam2med utility is published result of its work in SALOME VISU module (by
default). 

3. Connection to SALOME functionality within Python
---------------------------------------------------
A new "pysalome.py" script is introduced to simplify usage of SALOME
functionality from within Python code. Once loaded it whether connects to the
existing SALOME session, or launch a new one. So, by usage of this script it
is possible to unify writing of standalone and embedded Python functionality. 
